                "question"              => "How to Create, Work on, and Track a Client-Specific Task",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To create, work on, and track a client-specific task, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-20%2017-00-48%203c709eae93397f4d5616.jpg\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-20%2017-00-48%203c709eae93397f4d5616.jpg\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><em>NOTES:</em></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><em>To learn how to create a new Task, see </em><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q313\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Create a Client-Specific Task</a><em>.</em></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><em>To learn how to reply to a task, see </em>How to <a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q185\" class=\"blulinkun\">Reply to a Client-Specific Task</a><em>.</em></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><em>To learn how to mark a task as complete, see </em><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q186\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Mark a Client-Specific Task as Complete</a><em>.</em></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><em>To learn how to edit a task, see</em> <a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q183\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Edit a Client-Specific Task</a>.</li></ul>",
