                "faq_section_id"        => 59,
                "question"              => "How to Mark a Task as Complete",
                "answer"                => "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong>To Mark a Task as <span style=\"color:#000000;\">Complete:</span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Click <strong>Mark as complete</strong></span>. </span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select <strong>Yes </strong>to confirm that you want to mark the task as complete and remove it from the task list. </span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>NOTES:  1) To view a completed <strong>General Task</strong>, go to<strong> My Tasks</strong>, select <strong>Filter</strong>, and select <strong>Completed </strong>beneath <strong>Status</strong>. 2) To view a completed client-specific task, go to<strong> Clients</strong>, select the client’s name, and select <strong>File Notes</strong></em>.</span></span></p>",
