            array(
                "faq_id"                => 103,
                "faq_section_id"        => 83,
                "question"              => "How to Set-up/Edit Incoming Mail Server",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">To set-up/edit the Incoming Mail Server, follow the steps below:</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-10-25%2016-40-34%202edd51c5e2a8ad8f004e.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-10-25%2016-40-34%202edd51c5e2a8ad8f004e.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">NOTES:</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;font-size:18px;\">1. The <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Incoming </strong>and <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Outgoing </strong>settings are customizable for use with most email providers and accept both </span></span><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">POP3 </span></span></strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">and <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">IMAP </strong>protocols.</span> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">2. Prior to initiating the first upload from the mail server, it is recommended that you clean up your Inbox or move the contents of your Inbox to a separate folder so as to save your storage quota in Officio.</span> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">3. When selecting the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Server Type</strong> (i.e., <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">POP3 </strong>or <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">IMAP</strong>), consider the following:</span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li><strong>POP3 </strong>allows you to: leave a copy of the email on the original server, download headers or full messages, and fetch mail from a specific date onwards. It <u>does not sync automatically</u> with the mail server. Therefore, any changes you make in Officio (e.g., delete an email, move an email to a particular client file, etc.) <u>will not </u>appear on your mail server.</li><li><strong>IMAP </strong>allows you to: leave a copy of the email on the original server, download headers or full messages, and fetch mail from a specific date onwards. It also <u>syncs automatically</u> with the mail server. Therefore, any changes you make in Officio (e.g., delete an email, move an email to a particular client file, etc.) <u>will </u>appear on your mail server.</li></ul><p>4. The <strong>Mail </strong><strong>server </strong>name and <strong>Port </strong>number can typically be found in the support section of your ISP/email provider's website.</p><p>5. When selecting your <strong>Encryption </strong>type, consider the following:</p><ul><li><strong>None </strong>- selecting this option will ensure that a secure connection is <u>not </u>used when downloading email from the mail server. This option is <u>not recommended</u>, as it will not provide a secure connection when transmitting documents and communications on the internet.</li><li><strong>SSL </strong>- or Secure Sockets Layer, is a protocol used to securely transmit documents and communications on the Internet. Many email providers require SSL, but every email provider uses different server addresses, port numbers, and authentication methods.</li><li><strong>TLS </strong>- or Transport Layer Security, which is an encryption protocol used to securely transmit documents and communications on the Internet. TLS is an updated and more secure version of SSL.</li></ul><p>6. Your <strong>Username </strong>is either your email address or your email address without the domain name.</p>",
                "meta_tags"             => "change\nmodify\naccount\nreceived\nreceived messages\ncommunication",
                "featured"              => "N",
                "content_type"          => "text",
