                "client_view"           => "N",
                "inlinemanual_topic_id" => null,
            ),
            array(
                "faq_id"                => 104,
                "faq_section_id"        => 83,
                "question"              => "How to Set-up/Edit Outgoing Mail Server (SMTP Mail Server)",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">To set-up/edit <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Outgoing Mail Server (SMTP Mail Server)</strong>, follow the steps below:</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-11%2010-13-33%20a276951dc8e84ba3fd74.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-11%2010-13-33%20a276951dc8e84ba3fd74.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><em><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">NOTES:</span></em></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-style:italic;font-size:18px;\"><em>While you can use Officio's SMTP server, it's highly recommended that you use your own SMTP server for best routing of your outgoing emails.<br /></em></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-style:italic;font-size:18px;\">The <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">SMTP </strong>name and <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Port </strong>number can be found in the support section of your ISP/mail provider's website.</li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-style:italic;font-size:18px;\">The Username and Password are the same as that which you entered under the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Incoming Mail Server</strong> tab.</li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-style:italic;font-size:18px;\">It is recommended that you select the same <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Encryption </strong>type as that which was selected under the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Incoming Mail Server</strong> tab. The <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Encryption </strong>options are:</li></ul><ul style=\"list-style-type:square;\"><li style=\"font-style:italic;font-size:18px;\"><em><strong>None </strong>-selecting this option will ensure that a secure connection is NOT used when downloading email from the mail server. NOTE: This option is not recommended, as it will not provide a secure connection when transmitting documents and communications on the Internet.</em></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;\"><em><strong>SSL </strong>- or Secure Sockets Layer, which is a protocol used to securely transmit documents and communications </em><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>on the Internet. NOTE: Many email providers require SSL, but every email </em></span></span></em></span></span></em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>provider uses different server addresses, port numbers, and authentication methods.</em></span></span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em><br /></em></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">TLS</span></strong></em><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em> – or Transport Layer Security, which is an encryption protocol used to securely transmit documents and communications on the Internet. NOTE: TLS is an updated and more secure version of SSL. </em></span></span></li></ul><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><br /></p><ul style=\"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-size:18px;\"><em>Clicking <strong>Test Account Settings</strong> will send a test email to your original email account as well as to </em>Officio<em>.</em><em> NOTE: If you are using </em>Gmail <em>and receive an error message, follow the instructions provided </em><a href=\"https://support.google.com/mail/answer/7126229?rd=2&amp;visit_id=0-636160581000781010-301902674#cantsignin\" class=\"blulinkun\"><em>here</em></a><em>. <br /></em></li></ul>",
