                "question"              => "How to Save an Email Message to a Client's File",
                "answer"                => "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To Save an Email Message to a Client’s File:</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Go to <strong>Email</strong>.</span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select a message from either the <strong>Inbox</strong>, <strong>Sent</strong> folder, <strong>Drafts</strong> folder or <strong>Trash</strong>.</span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click <strong>Save to.</strong></span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select either <strong>Save to Case</strong> (or client) or <strong>Save to Prospect</strong></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Under <strong>Save to</strong>, select the name of the client to whose folder you want to save the message.</span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li>Check <strong>Save attachment(s) separately<em> </em></strong><em>(NOTE: This will save any attachments [e.g., PDF, Word, etc.] under the <strong>Clients'/Prospects' Documents</strong> folder)</em> or leave it unchecked to retain the attachment with the email message.</li>\n\t<li>Check <strong>Remove original email from Inbox after Saving to</strong> <em>(NOTE: This will remove the email message from the <strong>Inbox </strong>and have it appear only under the <strong>Clients'/Prospects' Documents</strong>)</em> or leave it unchecked to retain the email in the <strong>Inbox </strong>and save it to the new location.</li>\n</ol>",
