                "question"              => "How to Add an Automatic Task",
                "answer"                => "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong>To Add an Automatic Task:</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Go to <strong>Admin</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>Automatic Tasks</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>Add Task</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Type a <strong>Name</strong> for the task.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select the <strong>Trigger(s)</strong> that you want to use to initiate the task. <em>NOTES: 1) The <strong>Trigger</strong></em> <em>tells the system when to initiate the task. 2) You can select more than trigger, but they need to be added one at a time. </em></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select the <strong>Condition(s)</strong> for the task.<em> NOTES: 1) The <strong>Condition</strong> provides limitations on the task. 2) You can select more than condition, but they need to be added one at a time.</em></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select the <strong>Action</strong> for the task. <em>NOTE: The <strong>Action</strong> is what you want the system do to accomplish the task.</em></span></span></li>\n</ol>",
