                "question"              => "How to Add a Document Folder for All Clients",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">To add a document folder for all clients, follow the steps below:</span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-21%2013-49-06%205b331bedc6048022c06a.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-21%2013-49-06%205b331bedc6048022c06a.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><em>NOTES:</em></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;background-color:transparent;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><em>Newly created Top Level and/or Sub Folders will automatically be added to new client files only and not to existing client fi</em></span><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><em>les. </em></span></a><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><em>To apply the new document folder to a specific existing client, see </em></span></span><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q285\" class=\"blulinkun\"></a><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q285\" class=\"blulinkun\"></a><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q285\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Apply a New Document Folder to a Specific Existing Client</a></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><em>. </em></span></span></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><em>To give Roles access to the document folder, see </em></span></span><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q286\" class=\"blulinkun\"></a><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q286\" class=\"blulinkun\"></a><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><a href=\"/help/index/index?type=help#q286\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Give Roles Access to a New Document Folder</a></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><em>. For security purposes, new document folders will not automatically be available to all Roles.</em></span></span></li></ul>",
