                "question"              => "How to Edit a Client/Trust Account",
                "answer"                => "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong>To Edit a Client/Trust Account:</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Go to <strong>Admin</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>Client Account Settings</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>Add/Edit Client Account</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select a client/trust account that you want to edit.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>Edit Client Account</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Edit the client account details, as needed.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">View a list of all previous <strong>General reconciliation statements </strong>by clicking the dropdown arrow next to <strong>Last reconciled</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">View a list of all previous ICCRC reconciliation statements by clicking the dropdown arrow next to <strong>Last reconciled ICCRC</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Reset a previous reconciliation statement by:</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">            a. Clicking the dropdown arrow next to either <strong>Last reconciled</strong> or<strong> Last reconciled ICCRC</strong> and selecting the month </span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">                preceding the month you want to correct. <em>(NOTE: If you select <strong>reset</strong>, this will reset all previous reconciliation </em></span></span></p>\n\n<p><em><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">               statements. The only way to retrieve these statements is to re-generate them through </span></span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Client Account</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>.</em>)</span></span></em></p>\n\n<p><em><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">            </span></span></em><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">b. Clicking on <strong>Update Client Account</strong>. <em>(NOTES: 1) This will reset all reconcilation reports that were generated after the </em></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>                month you selected. 2) The reset only impacts the generated reconcilation report(s) and does not unassign  </em></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>                transactions.)</em></span></span></p>",
