                "question"              => "How to Manage Special Deposit Types",
                "answer"                => "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong>To Manage Special Deposit Types:</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Go to <strong>Admin</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>Client Account Settings</strong>.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select <strong>Special Deposit Types</strong> from the drop-down menu.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>+ Add</strong> to add a new <strong>Special Deposit Type</strong>. <em>NOTE: Delete the default text of <strong>New option</strong> and type a name for the new <strong>Special Deposit Type</strong> (e.g., <strong>Bank Error</strong>, <strong>Interest Earned</strong>, etc.).</em></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select the specific <strong>Special Deposit Type</strong> that you want to delete and click on <strong>Delete Selected</strong> to remove it from the system.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to apply any changes to the system.</span></span></li>\n</ol>",
