                "question"              => "How to Create a New Client Template",
                "answer"                => "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To Create a New Client Template:</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Go to <strong>Client Templates</strong>.</span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>+ New Template</strong>.<em> NOTE: Only administrators can grant access to the templates section of </em>Officio<em>. If you do not see this module, you do not have access to templates.</em></span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select <strong>New Email Template</strong> and use <strong>Settings</strong> to add fields from <em>Officio</em> that will automatically populate with the information in the system. Use <strong>Template Content</strong> to add customized text to the template.</span></span></span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select <strong>New Letter Template</strong> to add a document that you have created as part of a standard letter that is sent along with a particular message (e.g., invoice, welcome message, etc.).</span></span></span></span></li>\n</ol>",
