                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To search for a specific client, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Steps 1-3:</strong></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-21%2015-23-23%20dbe77ccc759b9cdd29c6.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-21%2015-23-23%20dbe77ccc759b9cdd29c6.png\" /></p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;font-size:18px;\"><em>NOTE: You can type any data from the Profile or Case Details section into the search bar to locate the client. Even if you type the first or last name of the client’s spouse or dependent child, </em>Officio<em> will find the main applicant.</em></span></span></span></span></p>",
