            array(
                "faq_id"                => 176,
                "faq_section_id"        => 90,
                "question"              => "How to Run an Advanced Client Search",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To run an advanced client search, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Steps 1-2:</strong></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-21%2015-36-15%206964cd980059978319b9.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-21%2015-36-15%206964cd980059978319b9.png\" /></strong></span></span></span></span><br /><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Steps 3-12:</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-21%2016-17-53%201c4aefb633b04bc97e53.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-21%2016-17-53%201c4aefb633b04bc97e53.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Steps 13-15:</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-21%2016-15-11%20cb7fe07792a3e1a3dd34.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-21%2016-15-11%20cb7fe07792a3e1a3dd34.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><em>NOTES: </em></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"font-style:italic;font-size:18px;\"><em>Regarding <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Step 3</strong>, selecting <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Case </strong>will search in the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Case Details</strong> section of all clients and selecting <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Profile </strong>will search in the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Profile </strong>section of all clients.</em></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\"><em>Regarding<strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"> Step 6</strong>, selecting <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">AND </strong>further restricts the search so that only clients who meet both criteria will appear on the list. Selecting <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">OR </strong>broadens the search so that clients who meet one or the two criteria will appear on the list. For example: you could search for all clients who were referred to you by a particular individual <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">AND </strong>all clients who owe you money.<br /></em></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\"><em>You can define relative dates for searches. For example, a \"<strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">60 days from today</strong>\" search will generate a completely different result today that it will in a month.</em></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\">Regarding <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Step 11</strong>, this feature is useful if you intend to apply the same search criteria again in the future. The <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Saved Search</strong> filters will generate a list based on the data in the system at the time the search is run. In other words, the clients who will be listed today may not be the same clients who will be listed a month from now.</li><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\">To view more information about the clients in the search result (or list), click <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Select Columns</strong> and select the additional columns of information you would like to view.</li><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\">Regarding <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Step 10</strong>, the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Reset </strong>doesn't delete any of the search criteria rows.</li></ul>",
