            array(
                "faq_id"                => 178,
                "faq_section_id"        => 90,
                "question"              => "How to Create/Edit the Client's Profile",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To create/edit the client’s profile, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;font-size:18px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Steps 1-6:</strong></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-24%2013-05-34%207330be3a0a34828d2fa6.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-24%2013-05-34%207330be3a0a34828d2fa6.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><em>NOTES:</em></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-style:italic;font-size:18px;\"><em>Regarding <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Step 3</strong>, the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Personal Information section</strong>, if you have more than one office, it's important to select the office to which the client belongs, as this will allow you to manage the access rights to that particular client's file. For example, if you </em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em> work with an overseas agent, you can allow the agent to only see the client files that are registered to that particular overseas office. To select the office for a particular client, follow the step below:<br /></em></span></span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;font-size:18px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><em>Step 7:</em></strong></span></span></p><p><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-24%2013-50-46%20149172f11f312fec49d3.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-24%2013-50-46%20149172f11f312fec49d3.png\" /></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"> <em>Regarding <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Step 5</strong>, the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Client Login Information</strong>, you can easily change the client’s username and/or password by clicking <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Change</strong> next to either <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Username</strong> or <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Password</strong>. See steps below:<br /></em></span></span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;font-size:18px;\"><em><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Steps 8-9:</strong></em></span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em><br /></em></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-24%2013-59-10%200e22c1df5e56f9764601.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-24%2013-59-10%200e22c1df5e56f9764601.png\" /></em></span></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>Regarding <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Step 5</strong>, select <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Enabled</strong> from <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Client Login Access</strong> to give the client access to his/her client file or select <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Disabled</strong> to remove client access to his/her client file. See steps below:<br /></em></span></span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;font-size:18px;\"><em><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Steps 10-11:</strong></em></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-24%2014-06-17%20bdbfe49b8af8f070500f.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-24%2014-06-17%20bdbfe49b8af8f070500f.png\" /></em></span></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"font-size:18px;\"><em>Regarding <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Step 6</strong>, upon</em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em> clicking <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Save</strong> the first time, a <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Username </strong>and <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Password </strong>are automatically generated. Upon confirming, </em>Officio <em>will send this information to your new client.</em></span></span></li></ul>",
