                "question"              => "How to Finalize a Form for Submission",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To Finalize a form for submission, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-02-09%2016-15-33%20ebab41601268f250b608.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-02-09%2016-15-33%20ebab41601268f250b608.png\" /></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;font-size:18px;\"><em>NOTES REGARDING <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">STEP 4</strong>: </em></span></span></span></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>The \"Finalize for Submission\" feature helps you comply with your record keeping requirements of retaining a copy of the actual submission as any future changes to the form will <u>not </u>impact the read-only finalized copy. You will still have access to the original fillable version of the form in the event you need to make further changes.</em></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>There is no limit to the number of times you can finalize the form as it simply creates another read-only copy of the form. </em></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>The finalized form can be found under the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Documents </strong>folder.<br /></em></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>The “Finalized” column to the right of the form name will be updated to reflect the date the form was finalized. </em></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>If the document has already been finalized, a pop-up box will appear indicating that a copy of the form already exists and asking if you would like to replace it, add a copy or cancel the request.</em></span></span></li></ul>",
