            array(
                "faq_id"                => 242,
                "faq_section_id"        => 44,
                "question"              => "What contributes to storage usage in Officio?",
                "answer"                => "<p><em>Officio </em>uses compression technology. Therefore, <em>Officio </em>tracks the amount of space it takes to store documents and email attachments that are uploaded to your account, rather than tracking the number of clients you have and the number of forms they use.</p>\n\n<p>In other words, if you chose not to use <em>Officio </em>email and not to upload any documents, your storage usage will be about 0GB.</p>",
