            array(
                "faq_id"                => 243,
                "faq_section_id"        => 44,
                "question"              => "Does Officio archive users' accounts?",
                "answer"                => "<p><em>Officio </em>archives users' accounts in the following instances:</p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>When a user has closed his/her practice.</li>\n\t<li>When a user is in the process of turning over his/her practice to new management.</li>\n\t<li>When a user needs to satisfy a regulatory requirement to retain closed client files and client records for no less than six years.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>In these situations, access to the archived accounts is on-demand, as needed, while existing client files are being closed. The access then becomes intermitent (i.e., a few times a year) until all client files are closed.</p>\n\n<p>The purpose of fully archived accounts is to retain a record of the closed client files. Subsequently, access is read-only for closed client files, including printing copies as needed. </p>",
                "meta_tags"             => "administration\ndata storage",
                "featured"              => "N",
                "content_type"          => "text",
                "order"                 => 29,
                "client_view"           => "N",
