                "faq_section_id"        => 80,
                "question"              => "What does \"Office\" mean?",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:18px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\">An <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Office</strong> in <em>Officio </em>can be set up to reflect one or more </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:18px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\">physical or virtual office spaces for your practice. The <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Office </strong>feature in <em>Officio </em>allows you to control the access rights to that space.</span></span></span></span></p><span style=\"font-size:18px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">\n\n</span><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:18px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\">For example, if you have an agent in an overseas office and a physical office space in Canada, it's recommended that you define this as two separate <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Offices</strong>. You will then have the tools to assign clients to the respective office and control who is permitted to see the client files belonging to that particular office.</span></span></span></span></p>",
