            array(
                "faq_id"                => 275,
                "faq_section_id"        => 63,
                "question"              => "How to Integrate Officio with an Existing Website",
                "answer"                => "<p>You can integrate two aspects of <em>Officio </em>with your existing website as follows:</p>\n\n<p><strong>1. Client portal</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>To embed the client portal, you will need an \"inline frame\" (i.e., \"i-frame\"), which allows a webpage to be displayed independently within another page.<em> NOTE: The client portal requires a minimuj of 920x1000 pixels to display properly.</em></li>\n\t<li>The custom HTML code that is needed to embed the client portal is: <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:Calibri, 'Calibri_MSFontService', sans-serif;font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"background-color:inherit;\">&lt;iframe src=”http://secure.officio.ca/?no_logo” style=”border:0px #FFFFFF none;” name=”clientLogin” scrolling=”yes” frameborder=”0″ marginheight=”0px” marginwidth=”0px” height=”1000px” width=”920px”&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>2. Prospects Web Questionnaire</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>To embed the prospects web questionnaire, you will need an \"inline frame\" (i.e., \"i-frame\"), which allows a webpage to be displayed independently within another page.<em> NOTE: The prospects web questionnaire requires a minimum of 920x1000 pixels to display properly. </em></li>\n\t<li>The custom HTML code that is needed to embed the prospects web questionnaire is: <span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:Calibri, 'Calibri_MSFontService', sans-serif;font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"background-color:inherit;\">&lt;iframe src=”</span></span><span style=\"background-color:#ffff99;font-family:Calibri, 'Calibri_MSFontService', sans-serif;font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"background-color:inherit;\">((insert questionnaire URL here))</span></span><span style=\"background-color:transparent;font-family:Calibri, 'Calibri_MSFontService', sans-serif;font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"background-color:inherit;\">” style=”border:0px #FFFFFF none;” name=”clientLogin” scrolling=”yes” frameborder=”0″ marginheight=”0px” marginwidth=”0px” height=”1000px” width=”920px”&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; </span></span></li>\n\t<li><em>NOTE: Where the prospects web questionnaire code says </em><span style=\"background-color:#ffff99;font-family:Calibri, 'Calibri_MSFontService', sans-serif;font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"background-color:inherit;\">((insert questionnaire URL here))</span></span><em>, insert your own unique URL. To locate your own unique URL:</em></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>          a. Go to <strong>Admin</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>          b. Click on <strong>Prospects Manager</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>          c. Click on <strong>Questionnaires</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>          d. Double click on the questionnaire that you want embedded on your existing website.</p>\n\n<p>          e. Under<strong> Default Settings</strong>, click <strong>Copy URL</strong>. <em>NOTE: You can also email this link directly to your prospects.</em></p>",
