                "faq_section_id"        => 67,
                "question"              => "How to Add the Client Portal to Your Website",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">To add the Client Portal to your website, follow the steps below:</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li>Review your webpage layout. See the Help topic titled: How to Maximize Your Webpage Layout to Integrate with Officio.</li><li>Review your website resolution. See the Help topic titled: How to Select the Best Resolution for Website Integration.</li><li>To embed the Officio logo-free Client Portal login page on your website, you will either need to use the following link (<a href=\"http://secure.officio.ca/?no_logo\" class=\"blulinkun\">https://secure.officio.ca/?no_logo</a>) or an element called an “IFrame”. IFrame stands for “inline frame” and it allows a webpage to be displayed within the context of another page, placing the document within its own independent frame. </li></ol><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">If you choose not to use the link/IFrame code, the Client Portal login page will have Officio's logo on it as follows:</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-09-01%2017-40-52%2060cbce54bec806288c30.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-09-01%2017-40-52%2060cbce54bec806288c30.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><br /></p>If you choose to use the link/IFrame code, the Client Portal login page will <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">not </strong>have Officio's logo  on it, as seen below. You can then use your own logo or branding to connect the Client Portal login page to your website.<br /><p></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-09-01%2017-51-56%201db7fe4b420e11ae6c43.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;\" alt=\"2021-09-01%2017-51-56%201db7fe4b420e11ae6c43.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><br /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Client Portal Login Code</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">The custom HTML code you may need to use to embed the Officio logo-free Client Portal login into your website is located below. You can give this code to your webmaster or you can copy and paste it if you are building the site yourself.</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">&lt;iframe src=”https://secure.officio.ca/?no_logo” style=”border:0px #FFFFFF none;” name=”clientLogin” scrolling=”yes” frameborder=”0″ marginheight=”0px” marginwidth=”0px” height=”1000px” width=”920px”&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</p>",
