            array(
                "faq_id"                => 303,
                "faq_section_id"        => 67,
                "question"              => "How to Maximize Your Webpage Layout to Integrate with Officio",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">The layout of your webpage refers to how information is sorted and presented on your website. Understanding layout is important to understanding how and where to integrate Officio with your website. </p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">Most websites fall into one of three layout types:</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">1. <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Left Menu</strong> - where the links to internal pages and content are on the left hand menu with a link to the main page from the header. When clicked, the link loads in the larger right-hand side frame. This type of layout is common to webpages made with <em>Drupal </em>(a programming language), drag-and-drop website builders, and <em>Wikis</em>.</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-09-01%2018-01-49%2082bfbcbed3c0c49e10c0.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-09-01%2018-01-49%2082bfbcbed3c0c49e10c0.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">2. <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Right Menu</strong> - where the links to internal pages and content are on the right-hand menu with a link to the main page from the header. When clicked, the link loads in the larger left-hand side frame. This type of layout is common to business sites built using blogging software.</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-09-01%2018-05-02%20044eb239aef3677d1a27.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-09-01%2018-05-02%20044eb239aef3677d1a27.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">3. <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Top Menu</strong> - where the menu is located at the top of the page, thus creating more space in which to display content. This type of layout is commonly built using <em>WordPress</em>, but can also be selected in drag-and-drop website builders. This is the best choice of website layout to use for embedding the assessment questionnaire or client login, as it gives more space in which to display the content.</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-09-02%2009-41-06%20a1917ed88c3e4c6f6904.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;\" alt=\"2021-09-02%2009-41-06%20a1917ed88c3e4c6f6904.png\" /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">Pages designed with one of these layouts are divided into segments called frames and the content in these frames can load independently of one another. </p>",
