            array(
                "faq_id"                => 304,
                "faq_section_id"        => 67,
                "question"              => "How to Select the Best Resolution for Website Integration",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">Both the Officio Client Portal login and the assessment questionnaire need a minimum of 920×1000 pixels of area to display properly. A pixel is one portion of what the screen can display, relative to its size. When you adjust the screen resolution of your monitor, the numbers it is giving you is the maximum pixels it can display (e.g. 1024×768). Most new PCs and monitors display the desktop with an average size of 1600×900 pixels or greater.<br /> <br />If you are going to use a website with a <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Left Menu</strong> or <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Right Menu</strong> layout, we recommend ensuring that the main body frame is at least 920 pixels wide.</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">For example:</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-09-02%2009-51-06%205e6ebd5dc92f410eaf15.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-09-02%2009-51-06%205e6ebd5dc92f410eaf15.png\" /></p>",
