                "faq_section_id"        => 67,
                "question"              => "How to Add the Prospects Assessment Questionnaire to Your Website",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">To add the prospects assessment questionnaire to your website, follow the steps below:</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li>Review your webpage layout. See the Help topic titled: How to Maximize Your Webpage Layout to Integrate with Officio.</li><li>Review your website resolution. See the Help topic titled: How to Select the Best Resolution for Website Integration.</li><li>Use an element that is called an “IFrame”. IFrame stands for “inline frame” and it allows a webpage to be displayed within the context of another page, placing the document within its own independent frame. See below for an example of a Top Menu layout page with an IFrame displaying the first page of the Officio prospects assessment questionnaire:<br /><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-09-02%2010-00-46%204dc46c3c082f43e76c39.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-09-02%2010-00-46%204dc46c3c082f43e76c39.png\" /></li><li>Use the following prospects assessment questionnaire code on your website: &lt;iframe src=”<span style=\"background-color:rgb(247,218,100);\">((insert questionnaire URL here))</span>” style=”border:0px #FFFFFF none;” name=”clientLogin” scrolling=”yes” frameborder=”0″ marginheight=”0px” marginwidth=”0px” height=”1000px” width=”920px”&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</li><li>Copy your own unique URL for the prospects assessment questionnaire code from the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Prospects Manager </strong>of the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Admin </strong>module in Officio and past it into the code where it says: <span style=\"background-color:rgb(247,218,100);\">((insert questionnaire URL here))</span>. To locate your unique URL, follow the instructions in the screenshots below. <em>NOTE: You can also email your unique URL for the prospects assessment questionnaire to your prospects and you will receive their submissions under the <strong>Prospects </strong>module.</em></li></ol><p><strong>Steps a-e:</strong></p><p><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-10-22%2013-42-26%201b30bb9d82012ba6dae4.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;\" alt=\"2021-10-22%2013-42-26%201b30bb9d82012ba6dae4.png\" /></p><p><strong>Step f:</strong></p><p><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-10-22%2013-42-45%20e5bc86773f87f9a8e5c6.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;\" alt=\"2021-10-22%2013-42-45%20e5bc86773f87f9a8e5c6.png\" /></p><p><br /></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">      6. Insert the final prospects assessment questionnaire code into your website.</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><br /></p>",
