                "question"              => "How to Add a Form (Advanced)",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:700;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To add a form, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:700;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-06-07%2014-47-45%20f49090d307ec49babf44.jpg\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-06-07%2014-47-45%20f49090d307ec49babf44.jpg\" /></span></span></span></span></strong><br /></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li><strong style=\"font-weight:700;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Go to <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Clients</strong>.<br /></span></span></span></span></strong></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select a client.</span></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Forms</strong>.</span></span></span></span></li><li><strong style=\"font-weight:700;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">+ New </strong><strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Form</strong>.</span></span></span></span></strong></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:700;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select the family member</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"> <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">the form(s) are for</strong> (e.g.<em> Main Applicant, Spouse, Child, Sponsor, Other).  NOTES: 1) The information that appears in the form is pulled from the Profile section, so it is important that the Profile section has been completed prior to assigning forms. 2) If you need an extra form for a family member or if you don’t want to use the connectivity among the forms, simply chose “Other” under “Family Member” to open a blank form.</em></span></span></span></span></li><li><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Under <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Categorical Search</strong> or using the <strong>Keyword Search</strong></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">, select the client’s category of immigration/citizenship (e.g. Work in Canada).</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Select form(s) to add</strong> to the client file.<em> NOTES: Review each form to ensure that it is the current version of the official form. Upon opening the form, check to ensure the <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Save Form</strong> button is blue. If the button appears grey or if the button doesn’t appear, close the form and open it again. When you are finished editing the form, click <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Save Form</strong> and ensure that you have received the confirmation message prior to closing the form. If you tried to save but were unable to do so (e.g., failed internet connection), you can save the form locally on your hard drive and then try saving it to </em>Officio <em>again at a later time.</em></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select either <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Show ALL versions of the form(s)</strong> or <strong style=\"font-weight:700;\">Show only the LATEST version of form(s)</strong>.<em> Note: While the latest form would be used most frequently, it may be more favourable to your client's case to use an older version of the form provided it is still being accepted by IRCC.</em></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click <strong>+ New form</strong> to add the selected forms.</span></span></li></ol>",
