                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To create a client-specific task, follow the steps below:</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2022-01-20%2016-47-03%2056b0d89aff16f674610a.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2022-01-20%2016-47-03%2056b0d89aff16f674610a.png\" /></span></span></strong></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><em>NOTES:</em></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li style=\"font-size:18px;\"><em>When </em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>selecting a deadline that is a certain number of days (calendar or business) from the current date, </em>Officio <em>will </em><em>automatically calculate the deadline.</em></span></span></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;\"><em>When </em><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>selecting a deadline that is a certain number of days (calendar or business) either before or after a particular milestone (e.g., interview date, medical expiry date, etc.), you may not have entered the milestone date into the Profile yet. However, </em>Officio <em>will automatically calculate the deadline as soon as you enter the milestone.</em></span></span></li><li style=\"font-size:18px;font-style:italic;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>When s</em></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>electing a <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Priority Flag</strong> for the task, we recommend that you create your own internal legend for each colour (red, blue, yellow, green, </em></span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><em>orange, purple and clear).</em></span></li></ul><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">   </span></span></p>",
