                "question"              => "How to Set Up Your Retainer Schedule (Advanced)",
                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">To Set up Your Retainer Schedule:</span></span></strong> </span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><img src=\"https://cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-06-10%2015-06-03%209e56fc6cb940953db41b.jpg\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-06-10%2015-06-03%209e56fc6cb940953db41b.jpg\" /></span></span><img src=\"https://cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-06-10%2015-15-00%20e1ca92e810f1c5d685f0.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-06-10%2015-15-00%20e1ca92e810f1c5d685f0.png\" /></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Go to <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Clients</strong>.</span></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select a client.</span></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click on <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Accounting</strong> </span></span></span></span></li><li><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Click <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Payment schedule templates</strong>.</span></span></span></span></strong></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select a template from <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Create a New or Edit an existing Retainer Schedule Template</strong>. <em>NOTE: To create a new retainer schedule, select <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">New Template,</strong> type the details for the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Amount</strong>, <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Tax</strong>, <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Description</strong> and <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Due on</strong>.</em></span></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Select an <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Invoice template</strong> – either <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Do not generate invoice automatically</strong> or <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Invoice</strong>. <em>NOTES: 1) ICCRC does not permit contingency billing. Please refer to ICCRC’s </em>Retainer Agreement Regulation<em> for a definition of contingency billing. Examples of contingency billing may include, but are not limited to, payment being due upon the issuing of: the visa, the file number, a request for medicals, etc. ICCRC members are responsible for ensuring that they are not engaging in contingency billing when setting up milestones in the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Due on</strong> column of the <strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Define Retainer Schedule</strong> section. A good practice is to set milestones based on the scope of service being provided to your client. Please direct any questions to ICCRC. 2) When a payment become due, it will automatically post as a balance due and you will receive a reminder message.</em></span></span> </span></span></li></ol>",
