                "answer"                => "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\">To configure My Email (i.e., link your existing email account to Officio), follow the steps below:</p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:bolder;\">Steps 1-7:</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1rem;\"><img src=\"//cahelpcenter.s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/content_images/0/2021-10-22%2015-48-28%208dbbbe3b7658b7d4b666.png\" style=\"vertical-align:top;margin:5px auto;text-align:center;border-style:none;padding:0px 1px;\" alt=\"2021-10-22%2015-48-28%208dbbbe3b7658b7d4b666.png\" /></p><p>For help on how to set-up the General Settings tab, review the <a href=\"https://test.officio.ca/help/index/index?type=help#q102\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Set-up/Edit Email General Settings</a> Help topic.</p><p>For help on how to set-up the Incoming Mail Server tab, review the <a href=\"https://test.officio.ca/help/index/index?type=help#q103\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Set-up/Edit Incoming Mail Server </a>Help topic.</p><p>For help on how to set-up the Outgoing Mail Server (SMTP Mail Server) tab, review the <a href=\"https://test.officio.ca/help/index/index?type=help#q104\" class=\"blulinkun\">How to Set-up/Edit Outgoing Mail Server (SMTP Mail Server)</a> Help topic.</p>",
